{"id": "EUVD-2024-44576", "enisaUuid": "9e713274-d1c1-3fe0-a4f0-4cb771432d7d", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niommu/vt-d: Fix incorrect pci_for_each_dma_alias() for non-PCI devices\n\nPreviously, the domain_context_clear() function incorrectly called\npci_for_each_dma_alias() to set up context entries for non-PCI devices.\nThis could lead to kernel hangs or other unexpected behavior.\n\nAdd a check to only call pci_for_each_dma_alias() for PCI devices. For\nnon-PCI devices, domain_context_clear_one() is called directly.", "datePublished": "2024-11-05T17:07:38", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T22:25:32", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0bd9a30c22afb5da203386b811ec31429d2caa78", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cbfa3a83eba05240ce37839ed48280a05e8e8f6c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fe2e0b6cd00abea3efac66de1da22d844364c1b0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/04d6826ba7ba81213422276e96c90c6565169e1c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6e02a277f1db24fa039e23783c8921c7b0e5b1b3", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-50101", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/01/msg00001.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-50101"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "013c7d56-c6b4-38c1-96ca-4e2856737d40", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9a16ab9d640274b20813d2d17475e18d3e99d834 <04d6826ba7ba81213422276e96c90c6565169e1c"}, {"id": "06f2afaa-54fd-3e61-9c3d-113c3048a983", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "59862b869275c27beb25cda2054b59a8b5d04970 <cbfa3a83eba05240ce37839ed48280a05e8e8f6c"}, {"id": "0a3e8e36-8840-3532-9397-8ff1a8306251", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.7"}, {"id": "2bbe81b5-8de5-304e-8110-f0ce982ab4a5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.169"}, {"id": "39022b00-c89d-3c5b-836c-2357ee